5 STATE OF MAINE
6 SENATE
7 132ND LEGISLATURE
8 FIRST SPECIAL SESSION
9 COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to S.P. 251, L.D. 753, “An Act to Support an
10 Aroostook Adult Treatment and Recovery Court”
11 Amend the bill by striking out the title and substituting the following:
12 'An Act to Authorize the Use of Funds Resulting from the Issuance of Securities by
13 the Maine Governmental Facilities Authority for the Purpose of Developing or
14 Improving New or Existing Court Facilities in Penobscot County'
15 Amend the bill by striking out everything after the enacting clause and inserting the
16 following:
17 'Sec. 1. 4 MRSA §1610-I, as amended by PL 2023, c. 17, Pt. O, §1, is further
18 amended to read:
19 §1610-I. Additional securities; judicial branch
20 Notwithstanding any limitation on the amount of securities that may be issued pursuant
21 to section 1606, subsection 2, the authority may issue additional securities from time to
22 time in an aggregate amount not to exceed $95,600,000 outstanding at any one time for the
23 purposes of paying the costs associated with the planning, purchasing, financing, acquiring,
24 constructing, renovating, furnishing, equipping, improving, extending, enlarging and
25 consolidating new and existing facilities and projects relating to the judicial branch in the
26 counties of Oxford, Waldo, Penobscot and York, acquiring and improving property relating
27 to the judicial branch in Hancock County and 55 Lisbon Street in Lewiston, replacing and
28 upgrading ventilation systems in facilities relating to the judicial branch in Presque Isle,
29 Lewiston, Rockland, Skowhegan and West Bath, acquiring and improving property
30 adjacent to the Capital Judicial Center in Augusta for parking and acquiring and improving
31 property in Skowhegan for future expansion and planning for other court facilities.'
32 Amend the bill by relettering or renumbering any nonconsecutive Part letter or section
33 number to read consecutively.
